        "font_size": 10.020000457763672,
        "header_level": null,
        "is_bold": false,
        "text": "Discussion:  Off-loading is a process designed to preserve the confidentiality and integrity of audit records by moving the records from the primary system to a secondary or alternate system. It is a common process in systems with limited audit storage capacity; the audit storage is used only in a transitory fashion until the system can communicate with the secondary or alternate system designated for storing the audit records, at which point the information is transferred."
      },
